(160, 21, '2017-10-14 14:17:16', '2017-10-14 18:17:16', 'Mikey T\'s Wild Wacky Day Off (8.5 miles):\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/9rc8qIE.png\" />\r\n\r\nI would recommend running this route with someone who has done it before if it\'s your first time, but it just goes University blvd -&gt; Drexel st -&gt; sligo creek -&gt; south northwest -&gt; back to sph.\r\n\r\n(http://www.mapmyrun.com/routes/view/1821760106)\r\n\r\nBriggs Beltway Bash (7.5 miles):<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/JUZzRZM.png\" />\r\n\r\nThis one isn\'t too hard to follow, just run on the trolley trail towards hamster cage but don\'t turn towards hamster cage and keep running straight. Run on Rhode Island until you reach Sunnyside park, then follow the trail in the park to a tall building, then run back on Route 1 until you reach Cherry Hill, then take cherry chill back.\r\n\r\n(http://www.mapmyrun.com/routes/view/1821774887)\r\n\r\nCherry Kill (or Cherry don\'t get yourself killed) (9.5 miles):<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/baxtrOe.png\" />\r\n\r\nThis one is pretty easy to follow, but I would avoid doing it with a large group, as you have to run on Cherry Hill rd, which is <strong>extremely sketchy. </strong>Go down cherry chill, then when you get to the end take a left, follow cherry hill until you reach sellman road, then run up the big hill and take a right on Montgomery back to route 1, then back to cherry chill and back to campus.\r\n\r\n(http://www.mapmyrun.com/routes/view/1821782096)\r\n\r\nI\'ll add more routes as they are discovered. S/o to Colin for the names', 'New Routes!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-routes', '', '', '2017-10-14 14:17:16', '2017-10-14 18:17:16', '', 0, 'http://umdclubrunning.com/blog/?p=160', 0, 'post', '', 1),
