ay were the women’s and men’s 200m semi-finals. After running a time of 29.57s in the preliminaries, Lila Coffman doubled down with a time of 28.68s. This put her just one place out of qualifying for the finals on day two. Clay Buckman ran a time of 23.46s which put him just three places back from qualifying for finals.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After a day filled with all-americans, PRs, and many strong efforts we headed back to the hotel to get warm and rest up for day two.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I’ll leave all the touchy feely stuff for the day 2 recap.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'NIRCA Track and Field Nationals 2022', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '499-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-04-05 21:39:37', '2022-04-06 01:39:37', '', 499, 'http://umdclubrunning.com/blog/?p=511', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
