(600, 51, '2023-05-05 03:31:55', '2023-05-05 07:31:55', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All I see is matrices.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I wake up and I don\'t see a popcorn ceiling, I see a 1583 x 2329 matrix of little specs sprinkled above me.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I walk to the mirror and see not a face, but rather a 3 x 3 matrix bearing the shape of a smiley face.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I look at my shirtless torso and see a 3 x 2 matrix.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I continue to gaze downward and see not 2 balls, but a 1 x 2 matrix.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I struggle to open the bathroom door because I don\'t see a handle. Only a 1 x 1 matrix.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I make my way to the dining hall where I eat matrices.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I go to linear algebra where I learn about matrices, but it just feels like social studies.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I go to club running practice as I run along what some may call a sidewalk, but I call a 34934 x 1 matrix.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I make my way home and analyze the day, but rather than normal human reflection, I simply recall the organization of the world into delicate patters of rows and columns.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As I write this post I bang my fingers into the (roughly) 14 x 5 matrix that a simpler being may call a keyboard.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even the screen I view appears to me only as a 3840 x 2160 matrix of illuminated pixels.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As I try to fall asleep, I count sheep. They align into one large identity matrix, growing by 1 dimension for each passing moment.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I fall asleep with great difficulty, yet satisfied. The matrix lens of life is my burden to carry, but under the surface there seemingly exists an underlying bliss.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Best,</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>J | B | 0 | 0</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> B | U | S | H</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'All I See Is Matrices', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'all-i-see-is-matrices', '', '', '2023-05-05 03:35:52', '2023-05-05 07:35:52', '', 0, 'http://umdclubrunning.com/blog/?p=600', 0, 'post', '', 2),
